frus:attachment.p:
1. Whereas the Germans, during their occupation of
                        Roumania, issued paper money to a value exceeding 2½ milliards, on the form
                        of notes of the Banca Generala Romana;

And whereas furthermore, according to their
ledgers a reserve of such printed notes to the value of 111 millions was
held in Berlin;

And whereas this recommendation referred to the
dispatch, to Vienna and Budapest, of an Inter-Allied Commission for the
purpose of ensuring the execution thereof;
